suggestion.Solution: Run the "atc -h" command to view the usage. For details, see ATC Instructions.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value for [--%s] is empty.

suggestion.Solution: Set a valid parameter value.

suggestion.Solution: Set a valid parameter value. The parameter value can only be true or false.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for parameter [--%s] is invalid. The value must be either 1 or 0.

suggestion.Solution: Set a valid parameter value. The parameter value can only be 1 or 0.

suggestion.Solution: 1.If the source model framework is Caffe, try again with a valid [--weight] argument.  2.If the source model framework is not Caffe, try again with a valid [--framework] argument.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], [--input_shape_range], and [--dynamic_dims] are mutually exclusive.

suggestion.Solution: 1.In dynamic shape scenarios, include only one of these options in your command line.  2.In static shape scenarios, remove these options from your command line.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for parameter [--log] is invalid.

suggestion.Solution: Select the value from [debug], [info], [warning], [error], and [null].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for parameter [--input_shape] is invalid. Shape values must be positive integers. The error value in the shape is %s

suggestion.Solution: 1. In static shape scenarios, set the shape values in [--input_shape] to positive integers. 2. In dynamic shape scenarios, add the related dynamic-input option in your command line, such as [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, but the dimension count of the dynamic-shape input configured in [--input_shape] is less than 1.

suggestion.Solution: 1. In static shape scenarios, remove the [--dynamic_batch_size] option from your command line. 2. In dynamic shape scenarios, set the corresponding axis of the dynamic-shape input in [--input_shape] to -1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for [--%s] is out of range.

suggestion.Solution: Run the "atc -h" command to view the usage. For details, see ATC Instructions.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for parameter [--%s] is invalid.

suggestion.Solution: Run the "atc -h" command to view the usage. For details, see ATC Instructions.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for [--%s] is invalid.

suggestion.Possible Cause: Try again with a valid argument.
suggestion.Solution: Run the "atc -h" command to view the usage. For details, see [ATC Instructions].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Opname [%s] specified in [--%s] is not found in the model, confirm whether this node name exists, or node is not split with the specified delimiter ';'

suggestion.Solution: Specify the name of an existing node in the graph.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Input Op [%s] specified in [--%s] is invalid. The Op type must be Data.

suggestion.Solution: Run the "atc -h" command to view the usage. For details, see ATC Instructions.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for shape [%s] is invalid. When [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, only batch size N can be -1 in [--input_shape].

suggestion.Possible Cause: When [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, only batch size N can be -1 in the shape.
suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid [--input_shape] argument. Make sure that non-batch size axes are not -1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: When [--dynamic_image_size] is included, only the height and width axes can be -1 in [--input_shape].

suggestion.Possible Cause: When [--dynamic_image_size] is included, only the height and width axes can be -1 in the shape.
suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid [--input_shape] argument. Make sure that axes other than height and width are not -1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for parameter [--dynamic_image_size] is invalid.

suggestion.Solution: The value must be formatted as [imagesize1_height,imagesize1_width;imagesize2_height,imagesize2_width]. Make sure that each profile has two dimensions.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Path for parameter [--%s] is too long. Keep the length within %s

suggestion.Solution: The path name exceeds the maximum length. Specify a valid path name.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Path [%s] for parameter [--%s] does not include the file name.

suggestion.Solution: Add the file name to the path.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for parameter [--singleop] is invalid.

suggestion.Possible Cause: The path does not exist or the file name is incorrect.
suggestion.Solution: Check whether the input file exists.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Failed to open file [%s] specified by [--singleop].

suggestion.Solution: Check the owner group and permission settings and ensure that the user who runs the ATC command has enough permission to open the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: File [%s] specified by [--singleop] is not a valid JSON file. Reason: %s

suggestion.Solution: Check that the file is in valid JSON format.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Empty Op name in the file specified by [--singleop].

suggestion.Solution: Check that no Op name is empty in the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Attribute [%s] of [%s] tensor [%s] for Op [%s] is invalid when [--singleop] is specified.

suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid tensor dtype and format.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Attribute name of Op [%s] is empty in the file specified by [--singleop].

suggestion.Solution: Check that no Op attribute name is empty in the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: There is an invalid value for attribute name [%s] of Op [%s] in the file specified by [--singleop].

suggestion.Solution: Check that no Op attribute value is invalid in the file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, but none of the nodes specified in [--input_shape] have a batch size equaling -1.

suggestion.Possible Cause: As [--dynamic_batch_size] is included, ensure that at least one of the nodes specified in [--input_shape] has a batch size equaling -1.
suggestion.Solution: 1. In static shape scenarios, remove the [--dynamic_batch_size] option from your command line. 2. In dynamic shape scenarios, set the corresponding axis of the dynamic-shape input in [--input_shape] to -1.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Parse json file [%s] failed, reason: %s. %s

suggestion.Solution: Check whether the json file is valid.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Nodes (for example, [%s]) connected to AIPP must not be of type fp16.

suggestion.Solution: 1. To enable AIPP, remove the nodes connected to AIPP from the [--input_fp16_nodes] argument.  2. If AIPP is not required, remove the [--insert_op_conf] option from your ATC command line.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] has [%s] profiles, which is less than the minimum ([%s]).

suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the number of profiles configured in [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] is at least the minimum.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] has [%s] profiles, which is greater than the maximum ([%s]).

suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the number of profiles configured in [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] is at most the maximum.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The profiles configured in [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] have inconsistent dimension counts. A profile has %s dimensions while another has %s dimensions.

suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the profiles configured in [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] have the same dimension count.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Dimension size [%s] is invalid. The value must be greater than 0.

suggestion.Solution: Set the shape values of each profile to positive in [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument have duplicate profiles.

suggestion.Solution: Check that the profiles configured in [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] are unique.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: As the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument is included, the corresponding nodes specified in [--input_shape] must have -1 axes and can not have '~'.

suggestion.Possible Cause: In dynamic shape scenarios, when [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size], or [--dynamic_dims] argument is included, the corresponding shape value in the input node must be set to -1 and can not have '~'.
suggestion.Solution:
1. In static shape scenarios, remove the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size] or [--dynamic_dims] option from your command line. 
 2. In dynamic multi-batch scenarios, set the corresponding axis of the dynamic-shape input in [--input_shape] to -1.
 3. In dynamic shape scenarios, remove the [--dynamic_batch_size], [--dynamic_image_size] or [--dynamic_dims] option from your command line and set [--input_shape] to -1 or n1~n2

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Failed to load the model from [%s].

suggestion.Solution: 1. Check that the model file is valid. 2. Check that the weight file or path is valid when model is more than 2G. 3. Check that the [--framework] argument matches the actual framework of the model file.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: GenerateOfflineModel execute failed.

suggestion.Possible Cause: Inner errors occurred during GenerateOfflineModel, possibly due to exceptions or unsupported functions.
suggestion.Solution: Refer to other printed error codes or view logs.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The number of -1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument exceeds the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].

suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the number of -1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument matches the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: The total number of -1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument is greater than the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].

suggestion.Solution: Ensure that the total number of -1 axes in the [--input_shape] argument is less than the dimension count per profile in [--dynamic_dims].

error_info_list.ErrMessage: [--%s] and [--%s] are mutually exclusive.

suggestion.Solution: Remove either of them and try again.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Value [%s] for parameter [--input_shape_range] or [dynamic_inputs_shape_range] is invalid. Reason: %s The value must be formatted as [%s].

suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid argument.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Dimension count [%s] configured in [--input_shape] does not match dimension count [%s] of the node.

suggestion.Solution: Set the dimension count in [--input_shape] according to the dimension count of the node.

error_info_list.ErrMessage: Current dimension size [%s] is not in the range of [%s–%s] specified by [--input_shape].

suggestion.Solution: Set the dimension size according to [--input_shape].

suggestion.Solution: Try again with a valid argument.
